{%- assign img1     = section.settings.image_1 -%}
{%- assign img2     = section.settings.image_2 -%}
{%- assign cta_url  = section.settings.cta_link -%}
{%- assign cta_text = section.settings.cta_text | default: 'See the ring I got her →' -%}

<article class="adv">

  {%- if img1 != blank -%}
    <div class="adv__hero">
      {{-
        img1
        | image_url: width: 800
        | image_tag:
          loading: 'eager',
          fetchpriority: 'high',
          widths: '390, 600, 800',
          sizes: '100vw',
          class: 'adv__hero-img',
          alt: ''
      -}}
    </div>
  {%- endif -%}

  <div class="adv__post">

    <p class="adv__byline">
      Posted by {{ section.settings.byline_name | default: 'Sarah M.' }}
      &middot;
      {{ section.settings.byline_date | default: 'May 2025' }}
    </p>

    <h1 class="adv__headline">
      I regret not taking better care of my dad. Here&rsquo;s what I did for my mom.
    </h1>

    <div class="adv__body">
      <p>I don&rsquo;t normally post stuff like this but I&rsquo;ve been sitting with it and I need to get it out.</p>
      <p>My dad passed away earlier this year. That photo was taken when I went to see him in the hospital. We thought he was going to be okay.</p>
      <p>He had a stroke. The doctors said it was from high blood pressure he&rsquo;d had for years and never managed. He was 71. He never complained, never really went to the doctor. We just assumed he was fine. I assumed he was fine.</p>
      <p>I lived 40 minutes away from my parents and barely went. I was always busy with work, my own life, whatever was happening that week. I kept telling myself I&rsquo;d visit more when things slowed down. They never did.</p>
      <p>The last time I talked to him, he asked if I was coming home for Easter. I said I&rsquo;d try. I never gave him a real answer. I think about that all the time.</p>
      <p>My mom is 70 now and living alone in their house. She tells me she&rsquo;s fine. But I said the same thing about my dad and I was wrong. So I don&rsquo;t really trust myself on that anymore.</p>
    </div>

    {%- if img2 != blank -%}
      <div class="adv__inline-wrap">
        {{-
          img2
          | image_url: width: 800
          | image_tag:
            loading: 'lazy',
            widths: '390, 600, 800',
            sizes: '100vw',
            class: 'adv__inline-img',
            alt: ''
        -}}
      </div>
    {%- endif -%}

    <div class="adv__body">
      <p>A friend of mine who&rsquo;s a doctor suggested a smart ring. Said families use them to track a parent&rsquo;s heart rate, blood oxygen and sleep from their phone. I hadn&rsquo;t heard of them before that.</p>
      <p>So I got one for my mom. It connects to an app on my phone and I can check her heart rate, her sleep, her blood oxygen anytime I want. Even when I haven&rsquo;t called in a few days. I just open the app and I can see she&rsquo;s okay.</p>
      <p>It doesn&rsquo;t fix the guilt. Nothing is going to fix the guilt. But it makes me feel a little less terrible about not being by her side every day.</p>
    </div>

    {%- if cta_url != blank -%}
      <a href="{{ cta_url }}" class="adv__btn">{{ cta_text }}</a>
    {%- endif -%}

    <div class="adv__body">
      <p>This morning her heart rate was normal. She&rsquo;d slept well. She was already up and moving.</p>
      <p>I just sat there for a second feeling relieved.</p>
      <p>I can&rsquo;t get my dad back. But I can make sure I don&rsquo;t lose her the same way.</p>
      <p>If you still have your parents, please just take care of them while you can. They&rsquo;re not going to be here forever &mdash; and you don&rsquo;t realize that until they&rsquo;re not.</p>
    </div>

    {%- if cta_url != blank -%}
      <a href="{{ cta_url }}" class="adv__btn">{{ cta_text }}</a>
    {%- endif -%}

  </div>
</article>

<style>
  *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; }

  .adv {
    background: #F2E8DC;
    min-height: 100vh;
    font-family: 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif;
    color: #2d2b28;
  }

  /* Hero image — full bleed, 5:4 crop on mobile */
  .adv__hero { width: 100%; }
  .adv__hero-img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    aspect-ratio: 5 / 4;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center top;
  }

  /* Article container */
  .adv__post {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 28px 20px 72px;
  }

  /* Byline */
  .adv__byline {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: #888;
    margin: 0 0 18px;
  }

  /* Headline */
  .adv__headline {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 26px;
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: #1f1d1a;
    margin: 0 0 24px;
  }

  /* Body copy */
  .adv__body { margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .adv__body p {
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0 0 20px;
  }

  /* Inline mid-story image */
  .adv__inline-wrap { margin: 32px 0; }
  .adv__inline-img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 6px;
  }

  /* CTA button — full width, tap-friendly */
  .adv__btn {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 100%;
    min-height: 52px;
    background: #1f1d1a;
    color: #F2E8DC;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin: 28px 0;
    padding: 14px 20px;
    text-align: center;
    -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;
  }
  .adv__btn:hover,
  .adv__btn:active { background: #2d2b28; }

  /* Desktop */
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .adv__hero-img  { aspect-ratio: auto; max-height: 560px; }
    .adv__headline  { font-size: 34px; }
    .adv__body p    { font-size: 18px; }
  }
</style>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Advertorial — Ring",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "image_picker",
      "id": "image_1",
      "label": "Hero image (top of page)"
    },
    {
      "type": "image_picker",
      "id": "image_2",
      "label": "Inline image (mid-story)"
    },
    {
      "type": "url",
      "id": "cta_link",
      "label": "CTA link — smart ring product page"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "cta_text",
      "label": "CTA button text",
      "default": "See the ring I got her →"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "byline_name",
      "label": "Byline name",
      "default": "Sarah M."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "byline_date",
      "label": "Byline date",
      "default": "May 2025"
    }
  ],
  "presets": [
    { "name": "Advertorial — Ring" }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
